[Patient] What are some affordable foods I can eat to manage my heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Try incorporating fruits, vegetables, whole grains, and lean proteins into your diet.
[Patient] Can you give me tips on how to shop for healthy foods on a tight budget?
[Healthcare Educator] Plan meals, make a list, buy in bulk, and look for sales to save money.
[Patient] I struggle to afford fresh produce. Any suggestions on where to find affordable options?
[Healthcare Educator] Look into local food assistance programs, community gardens, or farmer's markets for budget-friendly options.
[Patient] How can I make sure I'm eating heart-healthy foods even with limited resources?
[Healthcare Educator] Focus on nutrient-dense foods, use coupons, buy frozen fruits and veggies, and prioritize your health.